    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-09-11T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-09-11T10:00:00-05:00" n="190"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d190">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/1805</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Page</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-11T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1917, 4 p.m</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7150. Your 5399, September 8, 4 p.m. Foreign Office expresses tentatively
                    agreement with your views and tell me they know nothing of the desired loan of
                    200,000,000 Mexican dollars.</p>
                <p>They will however communicate with British Legation, Peking, and send me definite
                    answer later.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
